But men of our profes- sion cannot go where we will, except we be sent by the command of our captain, (the pro- vincial.”) “ Where, pray, does your captain dwell ?'’ eagerly inquired Marike. “In this very house,’' returned I. On hearing this he immediately caused himself to be led into our provincial’s chamber, and with importunate but vain entreaties, begged me for his companion. The provincial replied‚ that I was now ap- pointed to another station, but promised to send me in two years to his colony, and the provincial would have stood to his promise, had not my labours been needed amongst the Abipones.
